Steps to Reproduce:

1. code the following code and place it in an html file then format the file.
```html
<script>
      tag = document.createElement('script');
        src = "https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api";
        firstScriptTag = document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0];
        firstScriptTag.parentNode.insertBefore(tag, firstScriptTag);
  </script>
```

After the formatting it would look like:
```html
<script>
    document.createElement('script');
        "https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api";
        criptTag = document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0];
        criptTag.parentNode.insertBefore(tag, firstScriptTag);
</script>
```

I uninstalled VS Code, removed the 'code' folder in 'AppData\Roaming' and removed all extensions. The issue still occurs!

